data.name: Pumpkin Seed Butter Spread
data.quickTastyDescription: A creamy and nutritious spread made from roasted pumpkin seeds, perfect for toast or snacks!
detailedCookingInstructions: Spread pumpkin seeds on a baking sheet in a single layer.
Roast in the oven for about 8-10 minutes, or until fragrant and slightly golden.
Let the pumpkin seeds cool for a few minutes.
In a food processor, combine the roasted pumpkin seeds, olive oil, honey (or maple syrup), salt, and cinnamon (if using).
Blend until smooth and creamy, scraping down the sides as needed. This may take a few minutes.
Taste and adjust sweetness or salt as desired.
Transfer to a jar and store in the refrigerator.
data.modifiersForBase: Made creamy with olive oil and sweetened slightly with honey or maple syrup.
